# shadcn/ui Component Guidelines

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for all UI elements and components.

## Installation Requirements

- All UI components must be shadcn/ui components
- When a particular component is not installed, use the following command pattern:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
```

### Examples:
- To install button component: `npx shadcn@latest add button`
- To install card component: `npx shadcn@latest add card`
- To install input component: `npx shadcn@latest add input`

## Configuration

- shadcn/ui configuration is managed through [components.json](mdc:components.json)
- Component utilities are available in [src/lib/utils.ts](mdc:src/lib/utils.ts)

## Important Notes

- Do NOT use other UI libraries or create custom components when shadcn/ui alternatives exist
- Always check if a component is already available before installing
- Follow shadcn/ui component patterns and styling conventions
- Use the configured theme and design tokens from the shadcn/ui setup